Hello @ragizo 
You can use the `automatic_options` configuration parameter to handle the OPTIONS response automatically for you.

For example:
```
CORS(app, automatic_options=True)
@app.delete('/api/auth')
@auth.login_required
async def auth_logout(request):
    auth.logout_user(request)
    return json(None, status=OK)
```
_OR_ _(with the app config key)_
```
app = Sanic(__name__)
app.config['CORS_AUTOMATIC_OPTIONS'] = True
CORS(app)
@app.delete('/api/auth')
@auth.login_required
async def auth_logout(request):
    auth.logout_user(request)
    return json(None, status=OK)
```
_OR_ _(directly on the route with the cors decorator)_
```
@app.delete('/api/auth')
@auth.login_required
@cross_origin(app, automatic_options=True)
async def auth_logout(request):
    auth.logout_user(request)
    return json(None, status=OK)
```

